e Levelpath's 'future S2C' positioning.", "threat_level": "high", "last_confirmed": "2026-06-30T03:49:21.904587+05:30"}, {"date": "2026-03-06", "name": "SAP Ariba", "quote": "We're going to be looking at Coupa and Ariba as well as other vendors.", "change": "carried", "source": "Avoma 6 March 2026, Leon Pilosof", "status": "active", "sentiment": "neutral", "first_seen": "2026-06-26", "how_we_win": "Ariba is a legacy incumbent-style platform; Leon's 6 March comment about not wanting 'some legacy looking source-to-contract suite' suggests Ariba may be disadvantaged. Zycus wins on modern UX, AI agents, and agility vs Ariba's complexity and ERP lock-in. No active preference signals; monitor for Ariba advancing.", "threat_level": "medium", "last_confirmed": "2026-06-30T03:49:21.904587+05:30"}, {"date": "2026-03-06", "name": "Coupa", "quote": "We're going to be looking at Coupa and Ariba as well as other vendors.", "change": "carried", "source": "Avoma 6 March 2026, Leon Pilosof", "status": "active", "sentiment": "neutral", "first_seen": "2026-06-26", "how_we_win": "Coupa is a major S2C player but no buyer sentiment expressed. Likely in RFP for completeness. Zycus differentiates on AI-forward narrative (Merlin, ANA, agentic sourcing) and source-to-contract focus vs Coupa's broader but less specialized platform. No active engagement or preference signals; monitor for Coupa advancing to finalist round.", "threat_level": "medium", "last_confirmed": "2026-06-30T03:49:21.904587+05:30"}, {"date": "2026-03-06", "name": "GEP", "quote": "We are giving them an opportunity, they have a list of things they need to fix, the incumbent. Our agreement with them comes up end of December.", "change": "new", "source": "Avoma 6 March 2026, Leon Pilosof", "status": "incumbent", "sentiment": "negative", "first_seen": "2026-06-30T03:49:21.904587+05:30", "how_we_win": "GEP Quantum pain is acute and documented (metadata extraction <50%, lost notifications, no AI gains). Counter GEP by proving Zyc